All told, the avalanches were the worst in Austria since a series of snowslides killed 56 people in the village of Blons in January 1954.
In Austria's western Vorarlberg province, rescuers near Gargellen found a man and a woman Tuesday who were buried a day earlier when an avalanche swallowed a mountain restaurant, APA reported.
Tens of thousands of travelers were stranded in train stations, traffic jams and isolated resort towns across France, Italy Switzerland and Austria as the avalanches buried homes, roads and railways.
Scores of other resorts in Austria, Switzerland and France have been cut off from road access for days by the mounting danger of avalanches.
Rescuers in Evolene, Switzerland, found five more bodies Tuesday from avalanches on Sunday.
